/*

Your task is to write a SQL query that joins three tables (students, courses, and enrollments) and will create a matrix-like output that includes only "active" students and courses. An "active" student or course is defined as one that has at least one record in the enrollments table.

The matrix should indicate whether or not each active student is enrolled in each active course.

students:

student_id (integer) - The unique identifier for a student.
name (varchar) - The name of the student.
courses:

course_id (integer) - The unique identifier for a course.
course_name (varchar) - The name of the course.
enrollments:

student_id (integer) - The student identifier, a foreign key referencing students.
course_id (integer) - The course identifier, a foreign key referencing courses.
Constraints:

The output should only include students and courses that are active, i.e., they exist in the enrollments table.
The output columns should include a formatted string for students and courses, as well as a flag (is_exists) to indicate the relationship status.
The output should be sorted by student_id and then by course_id - both in ascending order
Expected output columns:

student (varchar) - A formatted string showing the student name and ID, like "John Doe (1)".
course (varchar) - A formatted string showing the course name and ID, like "Mathematics (101)".
is_exists (integer) - A flag indicating whether the student is enrolled in the course (1) or not (0).
GLHF!

Desired Output

The desired output should look like this:

student	course	is_exists
Miss Juan Connelly (1)	Law 487 (1)	1
Miss Juan Connelly (1)	Teaching 551 (2)	0
Miss Juan Connelly (1)	Business 555 (3)	1
Miss Juan Connelly (1)	Architectural Technology 572 (4)	0
Miss Juan Connelly (1)	Arts 479 (5)	0
...


*/




WITH s AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT st.student_id, st.name
    FROM students st
    JOIN enrollments en USING (student_id)        -- keeps only enrolled students
),
c AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT co.course_id, co.course_name
    FROM courses co
    JOIN enrollments en USING (course_id)         -- keeps only courses with enrollments
)
SELECT
    s.name        || ' (' || s.student_id || ')' AS student,
    c.course_name || ' (' || c.course_id  || ')' AS course,
    CASE WHEN en.student_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_exists
FROM s
CROSS JOIN c
LEFT JOIN enrollments en USING (student_id, course_id)
ORDER BY s.student_id, c.course_id;
